White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs made several announcements during the press briefing. He mentioned that the United States will host the next G20 summit in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. President Obama will meet with leaders representing 85 percent of the world's economy to discuss progress made since previous summits and further actions to ensure economic recovery. Gibbs also discussed President Obama's meeting with Judge Sotomayor and her views on constitutional interpretation. He stated that the President feels comfortable with her interpretation being similar to his own. Gibbs refused to disclose whether they discussed her views on the constitutional right to privacy. He also addressed questions about the closure of Chrysler dealerships and the controversy surrounding abuse photos from Iraq and Afghanistan.